<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1324,284,1190]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis box="[312,440,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Discussion</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Pesic &amp; Saboori &amp; Asadi &amp; Vafaei &amp; Sanatgar, 2006" authorityName="Pesic &amp; Saboori &amp; Asadi &amp; Vafaei &amp; Sanatgar" authorityYear="2006" box="[457,549,524,549]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[457,549,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">T. irana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[558,649,524,550]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the 
<emphasis box="[832,982,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">serratipalpis</emphasis>
species group, characterized by the presence on P­2 of a laterally compressed and serrate, hyaline ventrodistal projection (’flange’ sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiles, P. R." box="[575,713,604,630]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" pagination="191 - 236" refId="ref6544" refString="Wiles, P. R. (1997) Asian and Oriental Torrenticolidae Piersig, 1902 (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Lebertioidea): a revision of the family and description of new species of Torrenticola Piersig and Pseudotorrenticola Walter, from Southeast Asia. Journal of Natural History, 31, 191 - 236." type="journal article" year="1997">Wiles 1997</bibRefCitation>
), a similar, but more slender projection on P­3, and by the absence of a medial digitiform projection on P­4 (
<bibRefCitation author="Gerecke, R. &amp; Di Sabatino, A." box="[925,1270,644,670]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" pagination="287 - 334" refId="ref5968" refString="Gerecke, R. &amp; Di Sabatino, A. (1996) The water mites of the family Torrenticolidae Piersig, 1902 (Acari, Actinedida, Hydrachnellae) in springs and running waters of Sardinia and Corsica. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie Suppl., 107, 287 - 334." type="journal article" year="1996">Gerecke &amp; Di Sabatino 1996</bibRefCitation>
). By the absence of a fine denticulation on the ventral margins of P­2 and P­3, presence of ventral seta on P­2, relatively long median suture line of Cx­2+3 and the ventrodistal projection of P­2 not set off from the ventral margin of the segment, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pesic &amp; Saboori &amp; Asadi &amp; Vafaei &amp; Sanatgar, 2006" authorityName="Pesic &amp; Saboori &amp; Asadi &amp; Vafaei &amp; Sanatgar" authorityYear="2006" box="[1097,1191,764,789]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1097,1191,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">T. irana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1201,1294,764,790]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Viets, 1935)" baseAuthorityName="Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[449,804,804,830]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexipalpis">
<emphasis box="[449,639,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">T. convexipalpis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[656,795,804,830]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref6483" refString="Viets, K. (1935) Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda-Expedition. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Suppl. 13, Trop. Binnengewasser, 5, 484 - 594, 5, 595 - 738, Suppl. 14, Trop. Binnengewasser, 6, 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets, 1935</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, reported from Java. From 
<emphasis box="[1125,1322,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1125,1318,804,829]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexipalpis">T. convexipalpis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
it can be easily distinguished by the different shape of ventrodistal projection of P­2 (broad and subrectangular vs. strongly anteriorly directed in 
<taxonomicName box="[918,1097,884,909]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexipalis">
<emphasis box="[918,1097,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">T. convexipalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and much longer ventral seta of P­2 (not exceeding distal end of the ventrodistal projection in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1935" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Torrenticola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexipalpis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">T. convexipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1324,284,1190]" box="[312,824,1004,1030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis box="[312,437,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Etymology</emphasis>
: The species is named after 
<collectingCountry box="[770,821,1004,1030]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Iran</collectingCountry>
